##Millions of Americans feared losing their jobs, and 10,000 Italian medical students are starting work early

One, domestic add only 1 case, present a lot of"without symptom"input case

Figure 1

China Today: March 17 reported a total of 80894 confirmed cases, a new case in Wuhan. Suspected Cases in Hubei cleared to zero. A total of 12 cases (5 in Guangdong, 3 in Beijing, 3 in Shanghai and 1 in Sichuan) were newly reported. In Shandong, Sichuan, Yunnan and Guizhou provinces, asymptomatic infection has been found among returnees. The situation of "import of external prevention" is still serious.

Who Calls for "boldest action"

Figure 2

The number of new overseas cases expanded to 15,721. After Italy, Germany, Spain and the United States all added around 2,000. "every country, without exception, needs to take the most aggressive action to stop or slow down the [ new coronavirus ] threat, " Hans Günther von Kluge, director of the WHO's Regional Office for Europe, told a news conference

The Russian government decided to prohibit the entry of all foreign citizens and stateless persons from 18 March to 1 May.

Figure 3

The U. S. "space shuttle" seems to have finally filled up with fuel, since the epidemic, the first one-day increase of more than 1,000, and quickly toward 2,000. Germany is predictably on the fast track.

All 50 states and Washington have been hit

Figure 4

In the United States, the largest increase since the outbreak began, 1,764 new cases were confirmed in a single day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 6,461, an increase of 37.6 percent from the previous day. The first confirmed case has been identified by the West Virginia. So far, all 50 states and Washington have been hit.

On March 17 local time, the U.S. government announced that it will launch an economic stimulus package to ease the impact of the epidemic on the market and the economy. The total value of the package may be around $1 trillion, it is one of the largest federal emergency financial programs ever. Meanwhile, the US government intends to issue checks to Americans within two weeks, with each person receiving a subsidy of $1,000.

Four, European countries follow the blockade, Italy, medical graduates graduated ahead of schedule

Figure 5

The British Prime Minister, Boris Johnson, and the Chancellor of the Exchequer, Rishi Sunak, attended a joint press conference on the afternoon of March 17. The UK government is set to launch a series of emergency bail-outs to help small and medium-sized businesses in the crisis, including a # 330bn allocation to meet their credit needs. Pattrick Valens, the government's chief scientific adviser, admitted that the UK had yet to test all infected people for the virus and that priority would be given to those with severe symptoms. The UK has decided to step up testing following warnings and reminders from the WHO. Valens hopes that, through aggressive medical intervention, the total number of deaths in the UK could be less than 20,000.

From March 17 local time, Switzerland into a "state of emergency" , except for basic services, other public places and facilities will be closed.

The Norwegian government has decided to deport persons who do not have the right of abode in order to reduce the spread of new crown pneumonia.

Nineteen new coronavirus testing centres have been set up across Ireland to allow people to be tested for the virus without getting out of their cars.

On March 17th the List of Prime Minister of Luxembourg declared a three month state of emergency for the first time in history of Luxembourg.

Figure 6

To help the health services cope with the COVID-19 outbreak, Italian University Minister Gaetano Manfred, King of Sicily said the government would start work eight to nine months earlier for this year's medical school graduates, and exempt them from the compulsory examination before they obtain the qualification for employment. "This means that the immediate delivery of about 10,000 doctors to the national health system is essential to alleviate the country's ongoing doctor shortage. "

5. South Korea's cure rate is 18.3% , four consecutive days of double digit growth

Figure 7

As of March 18,1,540 patients with NCP in South Korea had been cured and released from isolation, with a cure rate of 18.3% .

To further prevent and control the new crown disease, South Korea's National Assembly passed 11.7 trillion won (about 66.3405 billion yuan) of the additional budget late on the night of 17. Specifically, the budget includes 1,0394 trillion won for Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province, the key areas of the epidemic; 1,163.8 trillion won for individual businesses; 148.3 billion won for responding to the epidemic; and 769.6 billion won for stabilizing people's livelihood An additional 241.8 bn won for low-cost Airlines and other sectors hit by the outbreak.

The city of Seoul, South Korea, is offering "disaster emergency living expenses" to residents who have been directly hit by the new pneumonia. 1,177,000 low-and middle-income households are given subsidies ranging from 300,000 to 500,000 won per household. This is a measure to overcome the national crisis and invigorate the regional economy, Seoul Mayor Park Won-soon said

6. Iran closes two Shiite shrines and releases 85,000 prisoners

Figure 8

Iran's Shia holy cities of Mashhad and Qom have shut down their holy sites for the first time, sparking protests. In addition to closing religious sites, Iranian Health Ministry officials have repeatedly urged people to stay at home and not to venture out, warning that "going shopping now in preparation for the New Year is tantamount to suicide" . But many people ignored the warnings, and shopping malls and restaurants remained open.

To prevent further spread of the epidemic, Iran's Ministry of Justice announced on March 17 again the release of 85,000 prisoners, including political prisoners.

[ special note: The above statistics, for the WHO official statistics before February 28, the data cut-off time is 17:00 China Standard Time; starting from February 28, the data from the "CAIJING" according to public statistics, the cut-off time is 9:00 China Standard Time. ]

7. Quick overview of the global epidemic:

[ $2 billion for a vaccine ] Richard Hatchett, CEO of the Alliance for Innovation in pandemic preparedness, estimates that it will take $2 billion over the next 12 to 18 months to develop a new cap vaccine fast enough.

[1 million unemployed ] the likelihood of a global recession is close to 100 percent, the former chairman of the White House Council of Economic Advisers, Kevin Hassett, told reporters. As many as 1M Americans could lose their jobs in March. The biggest previous unemployment crisis in the US was in March 2009, when 800,000 people lost their jobs in a single month.

Summary: Hubei existing suspected clear zero. Many provinces found that the presence of asymptomatic infection of returnees, "External Prevention of import" situation is still more serious. Nearly 2,000 new cases in the United States. Both the US and South Korea plan to hand out cash directly to the public to tide them over. Italy lets, medical students graduate early to join the fight against the plague.
